Rating: 4
These are my go-to chocolate chip cookies. I think I've been making them since the recipe first appeared in Gourmet, made them once and never looked back! I have to say that using quality dark chocolate chips (I usually go with Ghirardelli, or in a pinch Hershey's Special Dark) is an absolute must. The dough is perfectly salty, crisp on the outside and chewy in the center without being mushy-soft. I do make two key adjustments: do NOT melt the butter, and skip all of that business about measuring out 1 1/2 T of the third egg. I did that a few times at first, but there is no discernable difference if you put the whole darn egg in. Promise. Saves you a bit of time and yields a less greasy cookie. Be sure to flatten the lumps of dough with a wet palm or glass or else they will not bake evenly.

