I make these cookies ALL the time. My family and friends absolutely love them, although sometimes they do complain that they're a little on the big side. I highly recommend scooping some of the dough by 1/4 c., rolling them into balls, and then freezing them wrapped in wax paper and in a plastic baggie. When you want to use them, pop 'em on the cookie sheet, and by the time the oven has preheated, they're ready to flatten! Something about the freezing brings out the flavors--you get these great toffee notes! Perfect!

