Rating: 4
For mpax, the butter quality & flour make all the difference whether this cookie bakes chewy vs. crispy. I made my first batch with Challenge butter & Pilsbury flour, and they came out perfectly high & chewy. Then I used Trader Joe's butter & King Arthur flour. The TJ butter had too much moisture, and the King Arthur flour was pre-sifted too much at the factory. This 2nd batch baked up thin & crisp, spreading too much. A 3rd batch again using Challenge butter and this time Gold Medal flour again turned out chewy with good height.

