Rating: 4
This is my go to chocolate chip cookie recipe. Been making it since 2003 and it is consistently the most asked for baked item I make. Definitely melt the butter, but be sure to use a beater until it becomes pale and fluffy, it will happen just have patience. Sometime I will add 1/2-1 cup of cocoa powder to make an extra chocolaty cookie. I highly recommend a mix of semisweet and bittersweet chocolate chips, about 1 package of semi and 1/4-1/2 package of bittersweet. My true secret? Roll the cookie dough into balls and place on a cookie sheet wrapped in plastic wrap, once you get the whole batch made into balls freeze them. You can stick them right in the oven from the freezer for 16 minutes at 375. You will get a gooey/soft center and crispy outside. Plus you don't have to bake them all at once and you get fresh baked cookies when company comes over or you have a chocolate craving.

