Rating: 4
I am not kidding - this cookie recipe changed my life. I love chocolate chip cookies -- that is, when they are made by somebody who knows how to do it right. Mine have never had a good texture. Last year I buckled down to try to solve my inferior cookie problem. I spent months researching and trying recipes (unfortunately forgetting about epicurious for some reason), testing different baking sheets and mixers, and regulating the oven temp. -- striving to achieve the right combination of chewey and crispy. I tried cold butter, room temp, melted butter, room temp eggs, more soda, less soda, powder and soda, cream, cold batter, lots of mixing, narely mixing, hot oven, slow oven, etc.! Despite great efforts, my cookies were always doomed to be cakey or fluffy. Or occasionally puddles of grease or little rocks. After reading the reviews of this cookie, I decided to give it one more try. Guess what, this cookie is perfect! My husband and teenage kids said these were the best cookies they ever had. And they taste-tested every cookie I made. There is something amazingly perfect about this recipe. BTW, even though I am a pretty competent cook, I did not change a single detail (I guess I have no confidence when it comes to c.c. cookies) I followed the recipe exactly. Usually I cut back a little on the sugar because I don't have a sweet tooth, but I did not even do that this time. This recipe is perfect exactly as it is (even the quirky egg amount!) Thanks Gourmet -- my only regret is that I did not see/try this recipe a few years ago!

