Rating: 3
Very good (I'm still searching for my perfect recipe, but these are about the closest I've found so far). My 5 year old and 47 year old both ate more than their fair share, and the neighborhood kids and moms joined in the fun. Although I'm a chocoholic, I couldn't eat too many because they are so rich, but that's not a bad thing. Milk is a necessary and delicious accompaniment. Following other reviewers, we increased the brown sugar by .25C and decreased white sugar by same amount. We also decreased the salt to 1t and increased the vanilla to 2t. Used a coffee measuring spoon as the scoop, and baked for about 11 minutes after pressing down a bit. As another reviewer said, if you use a non- stick pan, you don't need the waxed paper (we did half with and half without -- no difference). Chock-full of ooey-gooey chips -- that's a good thing. Can't wait to try tomorrow for the day after effect I've read about.

