This recipe was great. Rich, delicious, chewy cookies that are sizeable like premium cookies you get at a cafe or deli. Watch the oven with this one - 13 mins @ 375 (I used an oven thermometer) was a little too long in my oven. This recipe is great on its own, but you can get creative with scrumptious results - I like cutting the chocolate chips down to 12 ounces, then adding 1/2-3/4 cup of shredded coconut, and 1/2-3/4 cup chopped walnuts. Chunky and delicious!

