Rating: 1
I made these cookies according to the recipe and they turned out very flat, a bit hard, and very chewy. I prefer a thicker, less chewy cookie, so I'm not happy with them. Also, they're a bit too sweet for me. For the first batch, I tried the original size the recipe suggested, and found them to be WAY too big. For later batches, I just used a heaping teaspoonful of dough and cut the cooking time down to about 9 or 10 minutes. Also, I agree with an earlier reviewer--it is not necessary to flatten the dough, since it spreads out regardless. Lastly, I didn't get the purpose of using wax paper. I forgot to use it for the first batch, but then used it for subsequent batches, and it didn't seem to matter. Overall, I'm not impressed.

