I LOVE these cookies. My friends and co-workers LOVE these cookies. In fact a high profile event during LA's Awards Season always request I bake these cookies for celebs, writers, & directors to munch on. The key to making this recipe work is the ingredients. I use Plugra butter, Callebaut semi-sweet chips, unbleached Pastry Flour, and Nielsen Massey Madagascar Bourbon Vanilla. These ingredients are a little bit more expensive, but so worth the cost. Also, I use Silpat mats to bake the cookies on. Again, a little pricey, but you'll have these mats forever. This recipe has never let me down. :0)

Rating: 3
Liked the texture of these. The only changes I made, based on others' recommendations, were to add a touch more vanilla and to use 3/4 butter and 1/4 shortening (I used the new Crisco trans-fat-free kind), because I think they flatten less with the shortening. I used a 1/8 cup measure, flattened the dough slightly, refrigerated the shaped cookies for a few minutes, and baked 11 minutes on an insulated cookie sheet. Ate three at one sitting . . .

