If you refrigerate the dough till chilled and then bake them cold the cookies remain thicker and keep a soft gooey center that you expect out of a fresh baked cookie. They will also stay soft in the middle for up to 3 days in an airtight container. Last little bit, I always add about 1/4 teaspoon of extra vanilla.

